snippet: Pornanong Phatlum of Thailand birdied seven of the first 10 holes and finished with a seven-under-par 65 to take a three-stroke lead in the L.P.G.A. Malaysia in Kuala Lumpur.
abstract: Pornanong Phatlum of Thailand takes a three-stroke lead in the LPGA Malaysia in Kuala Lumpur; other golf news noted.
lead_paragraph: Pornanong Phatlum of Thailand birdied seven of the first 10 holes and finished with a seven-under-par 65 to take a three-stroke lead in the L.P.G.A. Malaysia in Kuala Lumpur.
